<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1><i class="fa-brands fa-xing" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>TENSIV User Guide</h1>
        
        <br>
        <section>
            <h4> Adding a Product</h4>
            <p>To add a new product, navigate to the "Add Product" section on the Navbar. Fill in the necessary details such as Name ,Sku ,Capacity ,Quantity  and price, and click "Add". The product will be added to the inventory list.</p>
        </section>
        <br>
        
        <section>
            <h4>Problem in adding a Product?</h4>
            <p><ul><li>Please note that sku should be unique and should be a five digit number.</li>
                <li>Image should be in jpg,png and jpeg format only.
                <li>Price and quantity should be in number only</li>
                </li></ul>
            </p>
        </section>

        
        <br>
        <section>
            <h4> Viewing Products</h4>
            <p>You can view all added products on the Dashboard. Products will be displayed in a table format when you click  table on navbar where you can see details like product name, sku, price, and category.</p>
        </section>
        <br>

        <section>
            <h4> Editing a Product</h4>
            <p>To edit an existing product, go to the product list and click on the "Edit" button next to the desired product. Make the necessary changes and click "Update".</p>
        </section>
        <br>

        <section>
            <h4> Deleting a Product</h4>
            <p>If you wish to remove a product, click the "Delete" button next to the edit product in the product list. Confirm the deletion to remove the product from your inventory.</p>
        </section>
        <br>
        
        <section>
            <h4> Searching a Product</h4>
            <p>If you wish to search a product ,you can simply input the sku in navbar. Click the seacrh button next to the input box on navbar.</p>
        </section>
        <br>

        <section>
            <h4> Sorting Products</h4>
            <p>on the dashboard, you can sort products based on category .</p>
        </section>
        <br>

        <section>
            <h4>User Authentication</h4>
